language Essence 1.3

$ Social Golfers Problem — Formulation 10: Ternary Relation
$
$ Domain:  relation of (int(1..w) * int(1..g) * int(1..nGolfers))
$           with |relation| = w * g * s
$
$ Information carried by the domain:
$   - The total number of (week, group, golfer) assignments is w * g * s
$     (via the size attribute)
$   - Each tuple is unique (relation semantics — no duplicate triples)
$
$ Information NOT carried (must be constrained explicitly):
$   - Each golfer is in exactly one group per week (assignment)
$   - Each group has exactly s golfers per week (group size)
$
$ Explicit constraints needed:
$   1. Assignment constraint: each golfer in exactly one group per week
$   2. Group size constraint: each group has exactly s golfers per week
$   3. Pairing constraint: no pair of golfers shares a group more than once
$
$ Compared to Formulation 9 (3D boolean matrix):
$   - The relation is the set-based counterpart of the boolean matrix:
$     (i, j, p) in sched  iff  boolMatrix[i, j, p] = true
$   - The size constraint replaces the implicit "fully populated matrix"
$     assumption, explicitly stating the total number of assignments.
$   - This is the least structured formulation — all properties of the
$     schedule must be stated as explicit constraints.

given w, g, s : int(1..)

letting nGolfers be g * s

find sched : relation (size w * g * s) of (int(1..w) * int(1..g) * int(1..nGolfers))

$ Assignment constraint: each golfer is in exactly one group per week
such that
    forAll i : int(1..w) .
        forAll p : int(1..nGolfers) .
            (sum j : int(1..g) . toInt((i, j, p) in sched)) = 1,

$ Group size constraint: each group has exactly s golfers per week
such that
    forAll i : int(1..w) .
        forAll j : int(1..g) .
            (sum p : int(1..nGolfers) . toInt((i, j, p) in sched)) = s,

$ Pairing constraint: no pair of golfers shares a group more than once
such that
    forAll p1 : int(1..nGolfers) .
        forAll p2 : int(1..nGolfers) .
            p1 < p2 ->
            (sum i : int(1..w) .
                sum j : int(1..g) .
                    toInt((i, j, p1) in sched /\ (i, j, p2) in sched)
            ) <= 1
